Body:
The customer is not looking for a deleted user or group, but he's looking for the group the user is no longer part of because the user was removed from the group, but it still shows in AIC that the user is part of the group.

Â 

Under ADInventory_GroupView, I did not see the group in question.

I also looked under the AD_Changes_GroupMembershipChanges, but I did not see them.

We scheduled another meeting to investigate what happened since the groups are showing in AIC.
Next Steps Updated: At the next meeting, we will investigate what happened to the groups we searched for and could not find.
Description Updated: Some groups appear in AIC, but when you search for them in ADInventoy_GroupView, they do not appear among the groups.

Next Steps Updated: The customer will run a full ADI scan. 
If the full scan does not fix the issue, I will drop the domain and then rerun a full scan.

What We've Learned Updated: The group was part of the azure.
The Azure AD Inventory job was not set up as it should have been.
